SNA Descritive Analysis from “Projeto Redes de Atenção às pessoas que consomem álcool e outras Drogas em Juiz de Fora-MG Brazil” - SNArRDJF

Here you can find a basic script to analysis data from SNArRDJF - this script was elaborated considering its use for orther matrix adjacency data from SNArRDJF - Here we are going to analyse:

1 13_ACESSO E) Os canais de comunicação com este serviço são suficientes para realização de ações em conjunto. (var11)

3 Edges Newman-Girvan Edge-Betweenness - Non-Weighted

Edge betweenness Edge betweenness is equal to the number of shortest paths σst(e) from all vertices to all others that pass through that edge e

#Edge Betweenness
E(var11)$edge.betweenness_n<-edge.betweenness(var11, weights =E(var11)$equalone)
var11_edge.betweenness_n <-edge.betweenness(var11, weights =E(var11)$equalone)

4 Edge Betweenness Descriptive

summary(var11_edge.betweenness_n)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   1.000   7.727  19.920  44.470  55.040 862.300
sd(var11_edge.betweenness_n)
## [1] 65.69802

Edge betweenness Edge betweenness is equal to the number of shortest paths σst(e) from all vertices to all others that pass through that edge e

7 Betweenness Edge Dinamic Table

#Betweenness Measures Dinamic Table
#Getting  Measures
var11_edge.betweenness_n <-edge.betweenness(var11, weights =E(var11)$equalone)
var11_edge.betweenness <-edge.betweenness(var11, weights =E(var11)$var11)

#Creating a dataframe of measures
var11_df_betweenness <- data.frame(var11_edge.betweenness_n ,
var11_edge.betweenness) %>% round(1)

labels<-attr(E(var11), "vnames")
#edgebt<-cbind(round(var11_edge.betweenness,2),labels)

#Adding type
var11_df_betweenness <-cbind(var11_df_betweenness, labels)

#Adding names
names(var11_df_betweenness) <- c("Edge Betweenness", "Edge Betweenness Weighted", "Type")

#Ordering Variables
var11_df_betweenness<-var11_df_betweenness[c("Type","Edge Betweenness", "Edge Betweenness Weighted")]

7.1 General tabel for Betweenness

datatable(var11_df_betweenness, filter = 'top')

##Aggregating data from previous table - mean

aggdata_mean <-aggregate(var11_df_betweenness, by=list(var11_df_betweenness$Type), FUN=mean, na.rm=TRUE)

names(aggdata_mean) <- c("Group","Type","Betweenness(M)", "Betweenness Weighted(M)")
  
#Removing Type variable
aggdata_mean<-aggdata_mean[,-c(2)]

7.2 Aggregating data from previous table - sd

aggdata_sd <-aggregate(var11_df_betweenness, by=list(var11_df_betweenness$Type), FUN=sd, na.rm=TRUE) 

names(aggdata_sd) <- c("Group","Type","Betweenness(SD)", "Betweenness Weighted(SD)")

#Removing Type variable
aggdata_sd<-aggdata_sd[,-c(2)]

7.3 Merging mean and standart deviation

total_table<- merge(aggdata_mean,aggdata_sd,by="Group")

#Rounding
Group<-total_table[,c(1)] #Keeping group
total_table<-total_table[,-c(1)] %>% round(1) #Rouding
total_table<-cbind(Group,total_table) #Binding toghter

#Organizing Variabels
total_table<-total_table[c("Group","Betweenness(M)","Betweenness(SD)","Betweenness Weighted(M)", "Betweenness Weighted(SD)")]

7.4 Plotting final table with round

datatable(total_table, filter = 'top')

8 Network plotting based only on degree measures

#Set Seed
set.seed(123)
#Plotting based only on degree measures 
edge.start <- ends(var11, es=E(var11), names=F)[,1]

# Fixing ego
minC <- rep(-Inf, vcount(var11))
maxC <- rep(Inf, vcount(var11))
minC[1] <- maxC[1] <- 0
co <- layout_with_fr(var11, niter=10000, minx=minC, maxx=maxC,miny=minC, maxy=maxC, weights =E(var11)$edge.betweenness)

min(E(var11)$edge.betweenness)
## [1] 0
#PLotting
plot(var11, 
     layout=co,
     edge.color=V(var11)$color[edge.start],
     edge.arrow.size=E(var11)$edge.betweenness/10000*mean(E(var11)$edge.betweenness+1),
     edge.width=E(var11)$var11/10*mean((E(var11)$var11+1)),
     edge.curved = TRUE,
     vertex.size=log((degree(var11)+2))*(0.5*mean(degree(var11))),
     vertex.frame.color="#ffffff",
     vertex.label.color="black",
     vertex.label=get.vertex.attribute(var11,"LABEL_COR"),
     vertex.label.cex=log(degree(var11)+2)/mean(degree(var11)),
     vertex.label.dist=0,
     rescale=F,
     xlim=range(co[,1]), 
     ylim=range(co[,2]))
axis(1)
axis(2)


#Solving Problems with legend rendering 
a<-V(var11)$LABEL_COR
b<-V(var11)$color
c<-table(a,b)
d<-as.data.frame(c)
e<-subset(d, d$Freq>0)
f<-t(e$a)
g<-t(e$b)

#Adding Legend
legend(x=range(co[,1])[2], y=range(co[,2])[2],
       legend=as.character(f),
       pch=21,
       col = "#777777", 
       pt.bg=as.character(g),
       pt.cex=2,
       bty="n", 
       ncol=1,
       lty=1,
       cex = .5)

#Adding Title
  title("Network Edge Betweenness Sized - 13_ACESSO E) Os canais de comunicação com este serviço são suficientes para realização de ações em conjunto. (var11)", sub = "Source: from authors ", cex = .5)
  text(x=range(co[,1])[1], y=range(co[,2])[1], labels = 
   sprintf("Mean Betweenness : %.2f\n SD Betweenness : %.2f",
     mean(E(var11)$edge.betweenness), 
     sd(E(var11)$edge.betweenness)
   ))
